ket, without needing Docker. I wonder if we should consider adding an extra Maven dependency for `javax.servlet:javax.servlet-api`. The dependency tree shows that it's not version managed, but I'm checking if it's transitive to the compile process. Since the jetty-server compile depends on javax.servlet-api through jetty-servlet, it seems that any generated tests importing servlet classes should compile successfully.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra setup is needed. The resolved jetty-webapp artifact brings the Jetty runtime pieces needed for meaningful in-process WebAppContext/classloader coverage through normal Maven transitive dependencies, and typical usage is embedded/local webapp handling rather than an external service.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing compile failure is caused by Jetty 9.4 WebAppClassLoader.Context API changes, not by missing setup: isSystemClass/isServerClass now take Class<?> and the interface adds isServerResource/isSystemResource.\",\n    \"Avoid optional Jetty features such as JMX, JSP, annotations, or plus unless intentionally adding their optional modules; basic web.xml/static-content and classloader coverage should not need them.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_044caa870a42c55a016a42fe2396208190a023056dd0cc19f2\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 500, "output": 700, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28848, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782775321509, "responseId": "resp_044caa870a42c55a016a42fe1a00bc8190aee81dd88801096d"}, "toolResults": []}
